## Quick Start

1. **Analyze your video:**
   ```powershell
   .\scripts\analyze-video.ps1 -VideoPath "your-video.mp4"
   ```
   This tells you optimal frame extraction settings.

2. **Extract frames from video:** (requires FFmpeg on PATH)
   ```bash
   mkdir frames
   ffmpeg -i "your-video.mp4" -vf "fps=10,scale=1920:-1" -c:v libwebp -quality 80 "frames/frame_%04d.webp"
   ```

3. **Copy templates:**
   - Copy `resources/index-template.html` → `index.html`
   - Copy `resources/style-template.css` → `css/style.css`
   - Copy `resources/app-template.js` → `js/app.js`

4. **Customize:**
   - Update brand name, text sections, colors
   - Adjust animation timings and scroll ranges
   - Run `npx serve .` and scroll to test

## Key Requirements (Non-Negotiable)

✓ Lenis smooth scroll (not native scroll)  
✓ 4+ different animation types (never repeat consecutively)  
✓ Staggered reveals (label → heading → body → CTA)  
✓ Side-aligned text ONLY (40% zones, never centered)  
✓ Massive typography (hero 12rem+, headings 4rem+)  
✓ Canvas frame animation synced to scroll  
✓ Dark overlay for stats sections  
✓ CTA section persists at bottom (`data-persist="true"`)  
✓ Frame extraction rate 1.8-2.2x (completes by 55% scroll)  

